</p>
<p>In addition to calling this to upgrade a subscription plan, we <em>also</em> call this
at checkout, even if there is <em>no</em> subscription. The problem is that if payment
fails on checkout, this invoice will <em>still</em> exist, and Stripe will try again to
charge it. Imagine having your card be declined at checkout, only for the vendor
to try to charge it again later, without you ever having finished the checkout process!</p>
<p>Here's our rescue plan: if paying the invoice fails, we need to <em>close</em> it. By doing
that, Stripe will <em>not</em> try to pay it again.</p>
<p>To do that, surround the <code>pay()</code> line with a try-catch for the <code>\Stripe\Error\Card</code>
exception:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="23c9bca170">
